The article is a transcript of a conversation between Vice President Kamala Harris and Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen at the Freedman's Bank Forum. They discuss the importance of addressing racial disparities in the economy and the actions the administration is taking to promote economic equity. They highlight the need for intentional actions to close the wealth gap, increase access to capital for Black entrepreneurs, and support underserved communities. They also emphasize the role of community development financial institutions (CDFIs) and minority depository institutions (MDIs) in providing financial services to marginalized communities. The Vice President and Secretary Yellen mention the achievements of the administration, such as the Child Tax Credit and the Emergency Capital Investment Program, and call for continued collaboration with leaders from corporate America, advocacy nonprofits, and academia to eradicate the racial wealth divide. They also touch on the importance of protecting voting rights as a pillar of democracy and its connection to economic justice.